@push_leverage_positions
title: Push for more positions
view-if: parlament_coalition_leverage < 10
choose-if: parlament_coalition_push < erc_ciu_coalition_phase and erc_ciu_coalition_phase < 3
unavailable-subtitle: We've already pushed for more demands. [? if erc_ciu_coalition_phase < 3: We'll have to wait for the next round of negotiations to try again. ?]
on-arrival: {!
    if (Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase == 1) {
        Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 5;
    } else {
        Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 3;
    }
    Q.parlament_coalition_leverage += 4;
    Q.parlament_coalition_push += 1;
!}
go-to: changes

@send_back
title: Send this [? if erc_ciu_coalition_phase > 1: counter-?]proposal
view-if: parlament_coalition_changes
subtitle: [?if parlament_coalition_push >= erc_ciu_coalition_phase: Back-and-forth negotiations will take some time, but may give us the extra edge needed for a better deal. ?]
on-arrival: {!
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = true;
    if (Q.parlament_coalition_push >= Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
    } else {
        if (Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_vp == "erc" && Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase != 3) {
            Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
        }
        if (Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_interior == "erc" && Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_economy == "erc" && Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase < 2) {
            Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false;
        }
    }
!}
go-to: decision

@decision
title: decision
go-to: accept if parlament_coalition_proposal_accept; next_phase if parlament_coalition_proposal_accept = false

@next_phase
title: next phase
go-to: new_elections if erc_ciu_coalition_phase >= 3; new_phase_2 if not erc_ciu_coalition_phase >= 3

@new_phase_2
on-arrival: {!
    Q.parlament_coalition_changes = false;
    Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase += 1;
    Q.month_actions += 1;
    Q.independence_trust -= 2;

    // [+ parlament_current_ciu +]'s counter-proposal: claim the VP + ministries by leverage
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_foreign = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_health = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_education = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_territory = "erc";
    Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_bnl = "erc";

    var ciu_leverage = (Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_parlament_s"] / Q.parlament_coalition_erc_ciu_s)*55 + 12 - 3*Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase;
    if (Q.speaker_party == Q.parlament_current_ciu) ciu_leverage -= 10;

    if (ciu_leverage > 10) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_economy = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 10;
    }
    if (ciu_leverage > 10) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_interior = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 10;
    } else if (ciu_leverage > 7) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_health = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 7;
    }
    if (ciu_leverage > 6) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_foreign = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 6;
    }
    if (ciu_leverage > 5) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_bnl = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 5;
    }
    if (ciu_leverage > 5) {
        Q.parlament_coalition_proposal_territory = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
        ciu_leverage -= 5;
    }
!}

[+ parlament_current_ciu +]'s representatives were initially dubious about our proposal[? if parlament_coalition_proposal_vp = "erc": , especially our claim on the Vice-Presidency?]. We will have to wait until the [+ parlament_current_ciu +] and ERC negotiating teams reconvene to advance negotiations.

- @post_event: And so, time passes...

@accept
title: Accept proposal
view-if: not parlament_coalition_changes and erc_ciu_coalition_phase > 1
choose-if: not parlament_coalition_changes
unavailable-subtitle: We have proposed changes, which will require approval by [+ parlament_current_ciu +].
on-arrival: {!
    Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase = 0;
    Q.cat_coalition_disp = "<span style='color: var(--erc); font-style: italic;'>Sovereignty</span> <span style='color: var(--" + Q.parlament_current_ciu + "); font-style: italic;'>government</span>";
    Q.erc_in_gob = true;
    Q.erc_supporting = true;
    Q.cat_coalition = ["erc", Q.parlament_current_ciu];
    Q.cat_coalition_dissent = 0;

    Q.position_disp = "Generalitat";

    Q.cup_in_gob = false;
    Q.cup_supporting = false;

    Q.independence_trust += 10 * Q.erc_roadmap - (Q.year-2012);
!}

After some arduous negotiations, ERC and [+ parlament_current_ciu +] have reached an agreement to form a [+ cat_coalition_disp +]. As the leading partner, ERC will hold the Presidency. Some promises on independence commitments have been made, we'll have to monitor them closely as the legislature progresses.

- @parlament_coalition_resolve: A new government is formed

@new_elections
title: new elections
on-arrival: {!
    Q.erc_ciu_coalition_phase = 0;
    Q[Q.parlament_current_ciu + "_relations"] -= 5;
    Q.independence_trust -= 10;
    Q.snap_blame = Q.player_party;
    Q.snap_counterparty = Q.parlament_current_ciu;
    Q.snap_severity = 0.12;
!}
call: snap_election

After three rounds of negotiations, we've reached the end of the road. With no agreement in sight and no more time for back-and-forth, the only option left is to call for new elections and hope for a better result. Needless to say, neither ERC nor [+ parlament_current_ciu +] are happy about this outcome.

- @post_event: We'll have to see if we fare any better this time...
